practitioner.about:
Ms. Sara Muwafi is a Physiotherapist in the Department of Physiotherapy at Medcare Medical Centres. She obtained her Bachelor’s degree in Health Sciences (Physical Therapy) from the University of Sharjah and thereafter completed an Orthopaedic Manual Therapy and Exercise Diploma. She also holds a Certification in Clinical Dry Needling and a FIFA Diploma in Sports Medicine.  

She embarked on her career as a Physiotherapist while working at Adria Medical Center, Dubai. She also spent some time as a personal trainer at Acacia Advanced Medical Center, also in Dubai before joining Medcare as a Physiotherapist.

Ms. Muwafi’s expertise centres on sports injury and rehabilitation, musculoskeletal injury assessment, treatment and management, exercise therapy, pre and post-operation rehabilitation, and postural and structural alignment. She has proficiently treated patients with cervical pain, upper, mid and low back pain, facial palsy, multiple sclerosis, shoulder impingement, frozen shoulder and knee and ankle injuries.

During her leisure hours, she likes to play padel tennis and go hiking. She speaks Arabic and English.
